events.description: A fresh wave of corporate earnings reports from major companies including Eli Lilly, AMD, and Uber.
Upcoming report providing data on US private sector employment for January.

facts.fact_text: S&P 500 futures rose 0.3%, Nasdaq 100 futures gained 0.2%, and Dow Jones futures rose by nearly 200 points.

evidences.evidence_text: S&P 500 futures up 0.3%, Nasdaq 100 futures gaining 0.2%, and Dow Jones futures rising by nearly 200 points

facts.fact_text: Eli Lilly shares increased by over 6% in premarket trading after exceeding earnings and revenue expectations.

evidences.evidence_text: Eli Lilly shares surged more than 6% in premarket trading after the company reported earnings and revenue above expectations

facts.fact_text: AMD shares dropped nearly 9% following the release of their financial forecast.

evidences.evidence_text: AMD plunged nearly 9% after the company’s forecast disappointed

facts.fact_text: Uber shares fell 7.5% after missing both earnings and guidance targets.

evidences.evidence_text: Uber fell 7.5% following a miss on both earnings and guidance

claims.claim_text: Eli Lilly provided a positive financial outlook for the year 2026.
claims.author: Eli Lilly

claims.claim_text: The ADP employment report will offer valuable data regarding the state of the US labor market.

evidences.evidence_text: Traders are now awaiting the ADP employment report for further insight into US labour market conditions in January

claims.claim_text: AMD's future outlook was considered unsatisfactory by the market.

evidence.evidence_text: Investors turned their attention to a fresh wave of corporate earnings. Eli Lilly shares surged... US futures were higher
awaiting the ADP employment report for further insight into US labour market conditions
